lead_paragraph: A dispatch from Consul Norton, dated Picton Oct. 11, says that at least one hundred and fifty sail are ashore, amongst them the following: Schooner Harriet, Newell, of Harwich, lost two hands. The Lyon, of Castine, master, mate, and six hands lost.

headline.main: Further Particulars of the Storm at Prince Edward's Island-List of Vessels Ashore-Lives Lost &c.
